[2026-03-31 00:21:28.993] [PRINT]       "body_full": "Ask GitHub Copilot better questions from the start      \r\n\r\n\u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c     \r\n\r\n\"GitHub\"                                  \"GitHub\"                                            <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=263&elqTrackId=3beeddfb1037496e83f72d4bc926e898&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5EAD6BCF5D8CCEFC13B061A780B09A5EE9BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                            \r\n\r\nLevel up with Copilot \u2b06\ufe0f                   \r\n---------------------------------------------------------------\r\nNow that you\u2019ve got GitHub Copilot ready to go, today we\u2019re going to help you take advantage of its many capabilities. \r\n\r\nBelow, we\u2019ve gathered resources to amp up your productivity with our AI pair programmer, from a blog post about the basics of prompt engineering to a guide that\u2019ll help you figure out which AI model is right for your task. \r\n\r\nConsider your todo list done. \r\n\r\n\ud83d\udcdd The power of prompts                           \r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nEffective prompts make all the difference and we've pulled together a guide for GitHub Copilot prompt engineering. Whether you're experienced with AI prompts or new, this will help you get familiar with Copilot and prompt with confidence.                         \r\n\r\nGet the basics of prompt engineering <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8178&elqTrackId=09b39b62598e499eac1d69d46103d2c1&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5E57642946212D9EA6FBF5155FAB841959BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\ud83c\udf73 Get cooking with Copilot                          \r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nThe Copilot Chat cookbook is our library of sample prompts you can use to save time and effort with Copilot Chat. Explore our example prompts for generating unit tests, debugging invalid JSON, or making sense of legacy code. \r\n\r\nRead the cookbook <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8177&elqTrackId=450bb6fc6e8343ee87cba0cfa0715ff0&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5B106E4D9DD90F41341DD67E5FFCE8A349BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n\u2753 How to choose the right AI model \r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nWe\u2019re continuously adding support for new AI models to GitHub Copilot. That being said, we know it can be hard to keep up with so many new models being released all the time. So which model should you use? This guide will help you decide. \r\n\r\nGet our framework <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8176&elqTrackId=8c188cb8f60743069a92aed43aafe2e2&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF59ED5E3EBD548EC43757BB52A50E923509BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\"X\" <https://x.com/github?elqTrackId=088c53e52834499bbe48caebc5ea5a34&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF570A6B81F2D2C17BA8073A2CBFB5E65F09BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a \"Instagram\" <https://www.instagram.com/github/?elqTrackId=efe5410eae1342ed8c1456dbc3f8f8d7&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF51FECA97350FAA0747B87E750FC6225909BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a \"YouTube\" <https://www.youtube.com/github?elqTrackId=4b1fbabe41ea4b43bf0e05719b1c8a9a&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF5B39BFF54235DCA08E524215D61524F499BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a \"LinkedIn\" <https://www.linkedin.com/company/github/?elqTrackId=278f9f44c60644068e75c9181028c338&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF52287698ACFB61B50C881E56F1EEF59389BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a \"GitHub\" <https://github.com/?elqTrackId=bdc96bc1acc74bbe9d84b9cc93570ccb&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF529314B60A2A9E6F944EA85BCE8DBC7A19BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>\r\nPrivacy policy <https://help.github.com/articles/github-privacy-policy/?elqTrackId=393a56d77e5c48689fcd1e8c60aff26e&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF5E8EC21E6687D8748445E3900BA363AB49BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u2022 Terms of use <https://help.github.com/articles/github-terms-of-service/?elqTrackId=cc8cf764cc484eef9c4395039c733e33&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF51FEAE4449F51D7EE36C06B46960DE1319BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u2022 Contact us <https://docs.github.com/en/support/contacting-github-support?elqTrackId=6389f5e65ae1426ab3c12b12c2241da0&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF58DF2602F8C603FE1DA55C09457653C1E9BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u2022 Unsubscribe <https://app.github.media/e/u?s=88570519&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqak=8AF56BA7C6108615C570BD3710CB7C8D7E209BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>\r\nGitHub, Inc. \u2022 88 Colin P Kelly Jr Street \u2022 San Francisco, CA 94107\r\n\r\n",
