[2026-03-31 00:21:29.040] [PRINT]    ✓ latest_emails = [{'message_id': '19d2bb9f1ac0ec8a', 'thread_id': '19d2bb9f1ac0ec8a', 'from': 'Weaviate Newsletter <weaviate@mail.beehiiv.com>', 'subject': 'Enterprise Security, Multi-Vector Search, and Multimodal AI', 'date': 'Thu, 26 Mar 2026 19:57:14 +0000 (UTC)', 'internal_date': '1774555034000', 'label_ids': ['UNREAD', 'CATEGORY_UPDATES', 'INBOX'], 'body': 'Hello Weaviate Community! ☀️\n\nThis week, we\'re exploring how to **secure enterprise AI** deployments with robust access controls, diving into the next generation of search with **Multi-Vector representations**, and unlocking **multimodal retrieval** with Google\'s latest embedding model.\n\nFrom hardening production systems to enabling agents that reason across text, images, and video, we\'ve got fresh insights to power your AI stack.\n\nView image: ([link]\nFollow image link: (https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\nCaption: \n\n## Latest AI & tech insights\n\n_Explore our recent Weaviate content:_\n\n### Read\n\n* ✍️ **Securing Enterprise AI with Weaviate**: A complete guide on how to secure Weaviate enterprise deployments with OIDC, RBAC, and multi-tenant isolation. [Read the blog](https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\n\n### Watch\n\n* 🎙 **Multi-Vector Search with Amélie Chatelain and Antoine Chaffin**: Dive deep into Late Interaction models, ColBERT, and the future of retrieval. They discuss training multi-vector models, efficient retrieval with MUVERA and PLAID, and their work on ColBERT-Zero and PyLate. [Watch the full podcast](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=44GC3E-WbHU)\n\n* 📽️ **Google\'s New Multimodal Model - Gemini Embedding 2**: Learn how to build a multimodal PDF RAG pipeline using Google\'s first fully multimodal embedding model, now available in Weaviate. Query with text and retrieve relevant videos, images, or documents, all using the same model. [Watch the video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36He5BAKKLI)\n\n“🎧 **Tune into the Weaviate podcast on ****[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)****, ****[Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/show/4TlG6dnrWYdgN2YHpoSnM7?si=2b05d383738f4ca7)****, or ****[Apple Podcasts](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/weaviate-podcast/id1680897946)****.**“ — \n\n## Product highlights\n\n_Check out our latest product updates._\n\n* ⚙️\xa0**HFresh a new disk-based vector index**: Weaviate 1.36 introduced the HFresh vector index inspired by the\xa0[SPFresh algorithm](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.06981)\xa0("SPFresh: Incremental In-Place Update for Billion-Scale Vector Search"). HFresh is available as a\xa0**technical preview** in [Weaviate Cloud](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter) and open-source.\n\n* ⏱️ **Object TTL general availability**: Object TTL is\xa0**generally available**\xa0in Weaviate 1.36. TTL allows you to set an expiration time for objects in a collection. Expired objects are automatically removed through a background deletion process, enabling data lifecycle management without manual cleanup. Learn how to configure it in [our blog]([link]\n\n“💚 **Ready to start building?**\n\nJump right in and [spin up your free Sandbox cluster](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin) with **Weaviate Cloud.** Or **c**heck our [GitHub](https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate) and star us while you\'re there.\xa0⭐“ — \n\n## Hungry for more?\n\nHave a question or want to connect? Join our **[Weaviate Forum](https://forum.weaviate.io/)** to engage in community conversations.\n\nFollow our **[Blog](https://weaviate.io/blog)**, **[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/weaviate-io/)**, **[Twitter](https://x.com/weaviate_io)**, and **[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)** for more content updates.\n\nSee you in two weeks,\n\nKamil\n\n———\n\nYou are reading a plain text version of this post. For the best experience, copy and paste this link in your browser to view the post online:\nhttps://newsletter.weaviate.io/p/enterprise-security-multi-vector-search-and-multimodal-ai', 'has_attachments': False, 'attachments': [], 'body_full': 'Hello Weaviate Community! ☀️\r\n\r\nThis week, we\'re exploring how to **secure enterprise AI** deployments with robust access controls, diving into the next generation of search with **Multi-Vector representations**, and unlocking **multimodal retrieval** with Google\'s latest embedding model.\r\n\r\nFrom hardening production systems to enabling agents that reason across text, images, and video, we\'ve got fresh insights to power your AI stack.\r\n\r\nView image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/f7c0e427-79cb-4553-95dc-8488a4f1b788/Enterprise_Security-weaviate-blog-hero.png?t=1774554175)\r\nFollow image link: (https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\r\nCaption: \r\n\r\n## Latest AI & tech insights\r\n\r\n_Explore our recent Weaviate content:_\r\n\r\n### Read\r\n\r\n* ✍️ **Securing Enterprise AI with Weaviate**: A complete guide on how to secure Weaviate enterprise deployments with OIDC, RBAC, and multi-tenant isolation. [Read the blog](https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\r\n\r\n### Watch\r\n\r\n* 🎙 **Multi-Vector Search with Amélie Chatelain and Antoine Chaffin**: Dive deep into Late Interaction models, ColBERT, and the future of retrieval. They discuss training multi-vector models, efficient retrieval with MUVERA and PLAID, and their work on ColBERT-Zero and PyLate. [Watch the full podcast](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=44GC3E-WbHU)\r\n\r\n* 📽️ **Google\'s New Multimodal Model - Gemini Embedding 2**: Learn how to build a multimodal PDF RAG pipeline using Google\'s first fully multimodal embedding model, now available in Weaviate. Query with text and retrieve relevant videos, images, or documents, all using the same model. [Watch the video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36He5BAKKLI)\r\n\r\n“🎧 **Tune into the Weaviate podcast on ****[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)****, ****[Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/show/4TlG6dnrWYdgN2YHpoSnM7?si=2b05d383738f4ca7)****, or ****[Apple Podcasts](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/weaviate-podcast/id1680897946)****.**“ — \r\n\r\n## Product highlights\r\n\r\n_Check out our latest product updates._\r\n\r\n* ⚙️\xa0**HFresh a new disk-based vector index**: Weaviate 1.36 introduced the HFresh vector index inspired by the\xa0[SPFresh algorithm](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.06981)\xa0("SPFresh: Incremental In-Place Update for Billion-Scale Vector Search"). HFresh is available as a\xa0**technical preview** in [Weaviate Cloud](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter) and open-source.\r\n\r\n* ⏱️ **Object TTL general availability**: Object TTL is\xa0**generally available**\xa0in Weaviate 1.36. TTL allows you to set an expiration time for objects in a collection. Expired objects are automatically removed through a background deletion process, enabling data lifecycle management without manual cleanup. Learn how to configure it in [our blog](https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-1-36-release#object-ttl---general-availability?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter).\r\n\r\n“💚 **Ready to start building?**\r\n\r\nJump right in and [spin up your free Sandbox cluster](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin) with **Weaviate Cloud.** Or **c**heck our [GitHub](https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate) and star us while you\'re there.\xa0⭐“ — \r\n\r\n## Hungry for more?\r\n\r\nHave a question or want to connect? Join our **[Weaviate Forum](https://forum.weaviate.io/)** to engage in community conversations.\r\n\r\nFollow our **[Blog](https://weaviate.io/blog)**, **[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/weaviate-io/)**, **[Twitter](https://x.com/weaviate_io)**, and **[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)** for more content updates.\r\n\r\nSee you in two weeks,\r\n\r\nKamil\r\n\r\n\r\n———\r\n\r\nYou are reading a plain text version of this post. For the best experience, copy and paste this link in your browser to view the post online:\r\nhttps://newsletter.weaviate.io/p/enterprise-security-multi-vector-search-and-multimodal-ai\r\n', 'body_links': ['https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/f7c0e427-79cb-4553-95dc-8488a4f1b788/Enterprise_Security-weaviate-blog-hero.png?t=1774554175)', 'https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)', 'https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=44GC3E-WbHU)', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36He5BAKKLI)', 'https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)****,', 'https://open.spotify.com/show/4TlG6dnrWYdgN2YHpoSnM7?si=2b05d383738f4ca7)****,', 'https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/weaviate-podcast/id1680897946)****.**“', 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.06981)', 'https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)', 'https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-1-36-release#object-ttl---general-availability?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter).', 'https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin)', 'https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate)', 'https://forum.weaviate.io/)**', 'https://weaviate.io/blog)**,', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/weaviate-io/)**,', 'https://x.com/weaviate_io)**,', 'https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)**', 'https://newsletter.weaviate.io/p/enterprise-security-multi-vector-search-and-multimodal-ai']}, {'message_id': '19d26824583a0eef', 'thread_id': '19d26824583a0eef', 'from': 'GitHub <no-reply@github.com>', 'subject': 'Important Update to GitHub Copilot Interaction Data Usage Policy', 'date': 'Wed, 25 Mar 2026 19:32:42 +0000 (UTC)', 'internal_date': '1774467162000', 'label_ids': ['UNREAD', 'CATEGORY_UPDATES', 'INBOX'], 'body': '( https://github.com?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS )\n\nHi there,\n\nWe’re updating how GitHub uses data to improve AI-powered coding tools. From April 24 onward, your interactions with GitHub Copilot—including inputs, outputs, code snippets, and associated context—may be used to train and enhance AI models *unless you opt out*.\n\nIf you previously opted out of the setting allowing GitHub to collect this data for product improvements, your preference has been retained— your choice is preserved, and your data will not be used for training unless you opt in.\n\nThis approach aligns with established industry practices and will enable our models to deliver more context-aware AI coding assistance. We have tested this with Microsoft interaction data and have seen meaningful improvements, including increased acceptance rates in multiple languages.\n\nPlease review your settings and choose whether your interactions with Copilot can be leveraged for training AI models before this update goes into effect on April 24. To opt out or adjust your settings:\n\n* Go to *GitHub Account Settings*\n* Select *Copilot*\n* Choose whether to allow your data to be used for AI model training\n\nTo learn more, please refer to our blog post ( [link] ) and FAQ ( [link] ).\n\nPlease reach out to our support team ( [link] ) if you have any questions about this update. Thank you for your continued use of GitHub Copilot.\n\nSincerely,\nThe GitHub Team', 'has_attachments': False, 'attachments': [], 'body_full': '\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\xa0\u200c\r\n\r\n( https://github.com?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS )\r\n\r\nHi there,\r\n\r\nWe’re updating how GitHub uses data to improve AI-powered coding tools. From April 24 onward, your interactions with GitHub Copilot—including inputs, outputs, code snippets, and associated context—may be used to train and enhance AI models *unless you opt out*.\r\n\r\nIf you previously opted out of the setting allowing GitHub to collect this data for product improvements, your preference has been retained— your choice is preserved, and your data will not be used for training unless you opt in.\r\n\r\nThis approach aligns with established industry practices and will enable our models to deliver more context-aware AI coding assistance. We have tested this with Microsoft interaction data and have seen meaningful improvements, including increased acceptance rates in multiple languages.\r\n\r\nPlease review your settings and choose whether your interactions with Copilot can be leveraged for training AI models before this update goes into effect on April 24. To opt out or adjust your settings:\r\n\r\n* Go to *GitHub Account Settings*\r\n* Select *Copilot*\r\n* Choose whether to allow your data to be used for AI model training\r\n\r\nTo learn more, please refer to our blog post ( https://gh.io/AAzfaht?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS ) and FAQ ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/188488?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS ).\r\n\r\nPlease reach out to our support team ( https://docs.github.com/en/support/contacting-github-support?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS ) if you have any questions about this update. Thank you for your continued use of GitHub Copilot.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nThe GitHub Team\r\n\r\nPrivacy policy ( https://help.github.com/articles/github-privacy-policy/ ) • Terms of use ( https://help.github.com/articles/github-terms-of-service/ ) • Contact us ( https://docs.github.com/en/support/contacting-github-support )\r\n\r\nGitHub, Inc. \xa0•\xa0 88 Colin P Kelly Jr Street \xa0•\xa0 San Francisco, CA 94107\r\n\r\nYou are receiving this because you are a GitHub Copilot user.', 'body_links': ['https://github.com?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS', 'https://gh.io/AAzfaht?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS', 'https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/188488?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS', 'https://docs.github.com/en/support/contacting-github-support?utm_source=github&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY26MAR-WW-LCM-X-CBCE-AA-Devs-TX-701Kg000000PijXIAS']}, {'message_id': '19d24de574d34182', 'thread_id': '19d24de574d34182', 'from': 'GitHub <marketing@github.com>', 'subject': 'Next up, Copilot prompts that get work done', 'date': 'Wed, 25 Mar 2026 08:00:41 -0400', 'internal_date': '1774440041000', 'label_ids': ['UNREAD', 'IMPORTANT', 'CATEGORY_UPDATES', 'INBOX'], 'body': "Ask GitHub Copilot better questions from the start \n\nLevel up with Copilot ⬆️ \n---\nNow that you’ve got GitHub Copilot ready to go, today we’re going to help you take advantage of its many capabilities. \n\nBelow, we’ve gathered resources to amp up your productivity with our AI pair programmer, from a blog post about the basics of prompt engineering to a guide that’ll help you figure out which AI model is right for your task. \n\nConsider your todo list done. \n\n📝 The power of prompts \n---\nEffective prompts make all the difference and we've pulled together a guide for GitHub Copilot prompt engineering. Whether you're experienced with AI prompts or new, this will help you get familiar with Copilot and prompt with confidence. \n\nGet the basics of prompt engineering [link] \n\n🧑🍳 Get cooking with Copilot \n---\nThe Copilot Chat cookbook is our library of sample prompts you can use to save time and effort with Copilot Chat. Explore our example prompts for generating unit tests, debugging invalid JSON, or making sense of legacy code. \n\nRead the cookbook [link] \n\n❓ How to choose the right AI model \n---\nWe’re continuously adding support for new AI models to GitHub Copilot. That being said, we know it can be hard to keep up with so many new models being released all the time. So which model should you use? This guide will help you decide. \n\nGet our framework [link]", 'has_attachments': False, 'attachments': [], 'body_full': 'Ask GitHub Copilot better questions from the start      \r\n\r\n\u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c     \r\n\r\n"GitHub"                                  "GitHub"                                            <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=263&elqTrackId=3beeddfb1037496e83f72d4bc926e898&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5EAD6BCF5D8CCEFC13B061A780B09A5EE9BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                            \r\n\r\nLevel up with Copilot ⬆️                   \r\n---------------------------------------------------------------\r\nNow that you’ve got GitHub Copilot ready to go, today we’re going to help you take advantage of its many capabilities. \r\n\r\nBelow, we’ve gathered resources to amp up your productivity with our AI pair programmer, from a blog post about the basics of prompt engineering to a guide that’ll help you figure out which AI model is right for your task. \r\n\r\nConsider your todo list done. \r\n\r\n📝 The power of prompts                           \r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nEffective prompts make all the difference and we\'ve pulled together a guide for GitHub Copilot prompt engineering. Whether you\'re experienced with AI prompts or new, this will help you get familiar with Copilot and prompt with confidence.                         \r\n\r\nGet the basics of prompt engineering <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8178&elqTrackId=09b39b62598e499eac1d69d46103d2c1&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5E57642946212D9EA6FBF5155FAB841959BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n🧑\u200d🍳 Get cooking with Copilot                          \r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nThe Copilot Chat cookbook is our library of sample prompts you can use to save time and effort with Copilot Chat. Explore our example prompts for generating unit tests, debugging invalid JSON, or making sense of legacy code. \r\n\r\nRead the cookbook <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8177&elqTrackId=450bb6fc6e8343ee87cba0cfa0715ff0&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5B106E4D9DD90F41341DD67E5FFCE8A349BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n❓ How to choose the right AI model \r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nWe’re continuously adding support for new AI models to GitHub Copilot. That being said, we know it can be hard to keep up with so many new models being released all the time. So which model should you use? This guide will help you decide. \r\n\r\nGet our framework <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8176&elqTrackId=8c188cb8f60743069a92aed43aafe2e2&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqak=8AF59ED5E3EBD548EC43757BB52A50E923509BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>                                                            \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"X" <https://x.com/github?elqTrackId=088c53e52834499bbe48caebc5ea5a34&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF570A6B81F2D2C17BA8073A2CBFB5E65F09BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a "Instagram" <https://www.instagram.com/github/?elqTrackId=efe5410eae1342ed8c1456dbc3f8f8d7&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF51FECA97350FAA0747B87E750FC6225909BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a "YouTube" <https://www.youtube.com/github?elqTrackId=4b1fbabe41ea4b43bf0e05719b1c8a9a&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF5B39BFF54235DCA08E524215D61524F499BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a "LinkedIn" <https://www.linkedin.com/company/github/?elqTrackId=278f9f44c60644068e75c9181028c338&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF52287698ACFB61B50C881E56F1EEF59389BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> \u200a "GitHub" <https://github.com/?elqTrackId=bdc96bc1acc74bbe9d84b9cc93570ccb&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF529314B60A2A9E6F944EA85BCE8DBC7A19BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE>\r\nPrivacy policy <https://help.github.com/articles/github-privacy-policy/?elqTrackId=393a56d77e5c48689fcd1e8c60aff26e&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF5E8EC21E6687D8748445E3900BA363AB49BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> • Terms of use <https://help.github.com/articles/github-terms-of-service/?elqTrackId=cc8cf764cc484eef9c4395039c733e33&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF51FEAE4449F51D7EE36C06B46960DE1319BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> • Contact us <https://docs.github.com/en/support/contacting-github-support?elqTrackId=6389f5e65ae1426ab3c12b12c2241da0&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqaid=4554&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF58DF2602F8C603FE1DA55C09457653C1E9BC015C4D51FD248D0F3BBCF66661BBE> • Unsubscribe <https://app.github.media/e/u?s=88570519&elq=0ad56fce86a246aba2d021d61af68510&elqak=8AF56BA7C6108615C570BD3710CB7C8D7E209BC015C4D51FD248