[2026-03-31 00:21:29.227] [PRINT]             "body": "Hello Weaviate Community! \u2600\ufe0f\n\nThis week, we're exploring how to **secure enterprise AI** deployments with robust access controls, diving into the next generation of search with **Multi-Vector representations**, and unlocking **multimodal retrieval** with Google's latest embedding model.\n\nFrom hardening production systems to enabling agents that reason across text, images, and video, we've got fresh insights to power your AI stack.\n\nView image: ([link]\nFollow image link: (https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\nCaption: \n\n## Latest AI & tech insights\n\n_Explore our recent Weaviate content:_\n\n### Read\n\n* \u270d\ufe0f **Securing Enterprise AI with Weaviate**: A complete guide on how to secure Weaviate enterprise deployments with OIDC, RBAC, and multi-tenant isolation. [Read the blog](https://weaviate.io/blog/weaviate-security-enterprise?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter)\n\n### Watch\n\n* \ud83c\udf99 **Multi-Vector Search with Am\u00e9lie Chatelain and Antoine Chaffin**: Dive deep into Late Interaction models, ColBERT, and the future of retrieval. They discuss training multi-vector models, efficient retrieval with MUVERA and PLAID, and their work on ColBERT-Zero and PyLate. [Watch the full podcast](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=44GC3E-WbHU)\n\n* \ud83d\udcfd\ufe0f **Google's New Multimodal Model - Gemini Embedding 2**: Learn how to build a multimodal PDF RAG pipeline using Google's first fully multimodal embedding model, now available in Weaviate. Query with text and retrieve relevant videos, images, or documents, all using the same model. [Watch the video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36He5BAKKLI)\n\n\u201c\ud83c\udfa7 **Tune into the Weaviate podcast on ****[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)****, ****[Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/show/4TlG6dnrWYdgN2YHpoSnM7?si=2b05d383738f4ca7)****, or ****[Apple Podcasts](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/weaviate-podcast/id1680897946)****.**\u201c \u2014 \n\n## Product highlights\n\n_Check out our latest product updates._\n\n* \u2699\ufe0f\u00a0**HFresh a new disk-based vector index**: Weaviate 1.36 introduced the HFresh vector index inspired by the\u00a0[SPFresh algorithm](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.06981)\u00a0(\"SPFresh: Incremental In-Place Update for Billion-Scale Vector Search\"). HFresh is available as a\u00a0**technical preview** in [Weaviate Cloud](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin?utm_source=email&utm_medium=newsletter) and open-source.\n\n* \u23f1\ufe0f **Object TTL general availability**: Object TTL is\u00a0**generally available**\u00a0in Weaviate 1.36. TTL allows you to set an expiration time for objects in a collection. Expired objects are automatically removed through a background deletion process, enabling data lifecycle management without manual cleanup. Learn how to configure it in [our blog]([link]\n\n\u201c\ud83d\udc9a **Ready to start building?**\n\nJump right in and [spin up your free Sandbox cluster](https://console.weaviate.cloud/signin) with **Weaviate Cloud.** Or **c**heck our [GitHub](https://github.com/weaviate/weaviate) and star us while you're there.\u00a0\u2b50\u201c \u2014 \n\n## Hungry for more?\n\nHave a question or want to connect? Join our **[Weaviate Forum](https://forum.weaviate.io/)** to engage in community conversations.\n\nFollow our **[Blog](https://weaviate.io/blog)**, **[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/weaviate-io/)**, **[Twitter](https://x.com/weaviate_io)**, and **[YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@Weaviate)** for more content updates.\n\nSee you in two weeks,\n\nKamil\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\nYou are reading a plain text version of this post. For the best experience, copy and paste this link in your browser to view the post online:\nhttps://newsletter.weaviate.io/p/enterprise-security-multi-vector-search-and-multimodal-ai",
